Ref: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fgTGADljAeg&list=PLZlA0Gpn_vH9KXLvfhRS1J10UJZ0bZTj9&index=2


* To test routes

- The REST Client plugin is used in VS Code. 
  This is not required, Postman could be used instead

- To test routes using the plugin
   
    - create a file named route.rest

* route.rest example:

- The ### creates separate routes to test
- Click on the 'Send Request' link above each route to see the headers and response data returned by the route

GET http://localhost:3030/logs

###

GET http://localhost:3030/logs/15


POST http://localhost:3030/logs
Content-type: application/json

{
    "weekBeginning": "2021-02-03 22:10:57",
    "subject": "A subject",
    "task": "A task",
    "progress": "Some progress"
}


* Models

Example: 

const mongoose = require('mongoose')

const logSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
    weekBeginning: {
        type: Date,
        required: true,
        default: Date.now
    },
    subject: {
        type: String, // use a  custom type from a list of 
        required: true
    },
    task: {
        type: String,
        required: true
    },
    progress: {
        type: String,
        required: true
    }
})

/*
    - mongoose.model(NAME_OF_MODEL_IN_THE_DATABASE, NAME_OF_SCHEMA)
*/
module.exports = mongoose.model('Log', logSchema)